[
  "Ed Stack is CEO and largest individual shareholder of Dick's Sporting Goods. He will step down as CEO on Feb. 1, 2021 to become executive chairman. ",
  "His father, Dick Stack, founded the retailer in 1948 with a $300 loan from his grandmother. ",
  "Ed and his siblings bought the company from his father when it only had two stores in upstate New York.",
  "When his father retired in 1984, Ed took over as CEO and chairman.",
  "He took the company public in 2002. Dick's Sporting Goods had $8.5 billion in revenue in 2018 and 750 locations around the U.S."
]